  "analysis": "Great! Mailman3 is now running with multiple runners. The init script started successfully and also generated MTA alias maps. Now we need to create the mailing list 'reading-group' with subscription policy open. Also need to configure postfix to relay to mailman LMTP. The init script may have already updated postfix transport maps (since it said \"Generating MTA alias maps\"). Let's check /etc/postfix/main.cf for transport_maps and also check /etc/aliases. We'll also need to ensure the list's domain is local.edu. We'll create list with mailman create. Then set subscription policy to open. Also need to set list's posting policy maybe. Let's proceed.",
