  "analysis": "Error: subscription_policy is an enum, we cannot assign integer 1 directly. Need to assign the enum value SubscriptionPolicy.open. In the shell we can import SubscriptionPolicy from mailman.interfaces. Let's do that. Also need to use m.save? Actually the shell auto-commits? The error says no attribute 'save'. In mailman shell, changes are committed automatically when the shell exits? But we got an error due to wrong value. Let's fix subscription_policy by using SubscriptionPolicy.open. Also need to set advertise and send_welcome_message correctly. Let's do a new shell session with proper imports. Also we need to ensure postfix transport maps are set up. The mailman aliases command should have updated transport maps. Let's check /etc/postfix/mailman-transport.cfg or similar. We'll also need to ensure domain local.edu is added to relay_domains. Let's first fix list settings.",
