  "analysis": "Great, subscription policy set to open. Now need to configure postfix to relay messages to mailman LMTP. According to mailman documentation, we need to run 'mailman aliases' which generates transport maps and updates postfix configuration. However, we saw transport_maps empty and no mailman config. The mailman aliases command may have generated files in /etc/mailman3/postfix-*? Let's check. Also we need to ensure domain local.edu is added to relay_domains. Let's examine what mailman aliases actually does. We can also manually configure postfix using mailman's postfix integration. Let's check if there is a script /usr/lib/mailman3/bin/mailman-postfix. Let's search.",
